		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64613051"><p>Horrifying as the prospect is, if we want to keep adding people to the planet that's not the worst way to reduce stress on the environment.</p><p>Personally, I think we should be targeting a long term population reduction to a half billion or so.  Imagine humanity having 1/16th the environmental impact it currently does, or a higher average standard of living but still a net reduction in it.</p><p>Imagine going to a tourist spot and being able to do something other than shuffle through shoulder-to-shoulder with other tou<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
