		<div id="comment_body_64613095"><p>No. No. No. We're taking a step back here. Just remove the speed <b>limits</b>. Not the information, of course, the legality. They're a pretty stupid idea in the first place. Top speed in snow, rain, ice and clear road are all different. Posted speeds are for rain because they have to be. In clear weather, it makes perfect sense to do 5-10 mph over the limit. I've taken turns at 15 mph over the posted suggested speed and not felt centripetal force.</p><p>"Over the limit" is not a safety concern at all. Give us two condit<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64613095">

